  <sect1 id="pm-manager">
    <title>System State Information</title>
    <para>
      Some programs may want to know if the system is running on AC power,
      or running in a low power mode, for instance to disable index updating.
      These are the required DBUS methods for showing system state.
    </para>

    <para>
      DBUS Object Path: <literal>/org/gnome/PowerManager/Manager</literal>
    </para>

    <sect2 id="pm-ui-GetOnAc">
      <title>
        <literal>GetOnAc()</literal>
      </title>
      <para>
        Returns the system AC state, i.e. if we are not running on battery
        power.
        Note: This method may still return false on AC using a desktop system
        if the computer is using backup power from a monitored UPS.
      </para>
      <informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Direction</entry>
              <entry>Type</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>out</entry>
              <entry>boolean</entry>
              <entry>If the system is using AC power</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
    </sect2>

    <sect2 id="pm-ui-OnAcChanged">
      <title>
        <literal>OnAcChanged</literal>
      </title>
      <para>
        Signals the AC state has changed.
      </para>
      <informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
